gh. <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> is an easy target for <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials who complain of corruption and failure to stop the drug trafficig drug trafficking. The Mexicans say they do the best they can with limited resources. At his final meeting with <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>, last February, de la <LOCATION> Madrid </LOCATION> said bluntly the best way to fight the drugs was for citizens of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to stop using them.
