s, in the absence of increased burden-sharing by our allies, may simply be unaffordable.'' The new administration also needs to take steps to try to end the series of weapons purchasing scandals and high prices for spare parts. One improvement would be in the Pentagon office which oversees what is supposed to be the realistic testing of weapons, the <ORGANIZATION> GAO </ORGANIZATION> said. The usefulness of the current testing system `` has been limited because of insufficient resources to conduct testing, deferrel of certain critical tests until after the production decision, failure to simulate realistic battlefield conditions during testing and acceptance of products which do not meet the test criteria,'' it said.
