<HEAD>China's Surging Economy _ At a Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Surging China, b0694</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Here are some of figures that are available on <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s economy 10 years after the start of its drive for economic reform -LRB- dollars converted from yuan -RRB-: GROSS NATIONAL PRODUCT _ $ 270 billion. ANNUAL PER CAPITA INCOME _ Urban: doubled to $ 247; rural: tripled to $ 125. FOREIGN TRADE _ $ 80 billion, double 1980. FOREIGN INVESTMENT _ $ 10 billion -LRB- joint ventures and wholly owned factories -RRB-. INFLATION _ Officially 19 percent but believed to be 40 percent. CHIEF INDUSTRIES _ Textiles, cement, pig iron, steel. CHIEF IMPORTS _ Grain, iron an steel, motor vehicles and parts, chemical fertilizers. CHIEF CROPS _ <PERSON> Rice </PERSON>, wheat, soybeans, cotton. POPULATION _ 1.08 billion -LRB- 76 percent rural -RRB-.
