<HEAD>FOOD: Survey</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Chicken, fish and fresh vegetables rated the most healthy among foods in a survey of adult consumer habits, and more people consider pizza very good for you than they do pork. The results come from a 1987 <ORGANIZATION> Yankelovich </ORGANIZATION> Monitor Report, a national sampling survey reported in Successful Farming magazine. Chicken was the meat respondents were most likely to eat fairly regularly, the choice of 84 percent. Twenty percent rated beef as `` very good for you,'' 13 percent felt that way about pizza, followed by coffee -LRB- 10 percent -RRB- and pork. Of the adults sampled, 65 percent said they were eating the same amount of beef they did a year previous, 26 percent said they were eating less and 8 percent responded more.
