 The stock market suffered a broad setback today amid persistent worries about the dollar and interest rates. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 17.42 to 2,044.99 by noontime on Wall Street. Losers outnumbered gainers by more than 3 to 1 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 334 up, 1,014 down and 461 unchanged. After falling sharply since the election early this month, the dollar steadied late last week as central banks of the industrialized countries intervened to support it. But analysts said many investors remained skeptical that the dollar would be able to continue strengthening on its own. Indeed, it fell today against leading foreign currencies. At the same time, brokers said, many participants were taking a gloomy view of the market outlook, in part because of the competitive allure of short-term interest-bearing investments sporting yields of close to 8 percent. <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> climbed 2 -RRB- to 86 -RRB-. Directors extended until Nov. 29 the bidding competition to acquire the company. Losers among the blue chips included <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION>, down 1 -LRB- at 114 |; <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION>, down | at 41 -LCB-; <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION>, down -LCB- at 43 -RRB-, and <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Telegraph </ORGANIZATION>, down -RRB- at 27 <ORGANIZATION> Intel </ORGANIZATION> tumbled 3 | to 19 -LCB- in the over-the-counter market Late Friday the company said its revenues and earnings for the fourth quarter would fall short of third-quarter levels because of soft orders for its 80386 microprocessor chip. Other semiconductor issues followed <ORGANIZATION> Intel </ORGANIZATION> lower. <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> dropped ~ to 36 | and National Semiconductor -RRB- to 8 -LRB- The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks lost 1.17 to 149.01. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was down .46 at 286.21. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 56.28 million shares at noontime, against 53.49 million at the same point Friday.
