<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Walt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said its fourth-quarter profit was flat, but that its full-year earnings rose 17 percent, boosted by big-spending theme park patrons and a string of hit movies. <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> reported Monday its profit was $ 136.4 million, or 99 cents a share, in the fourth quarter, up marginally from $ 135.3 million, or 98 cents a share, in the fourth quarter of 1987. Sales for the quarter ended Sept. 30 were $ 1.01 billion, up 34 percent from $ 758.6 million a year ago. The results of a subsidiary that has since been sold are included in the figure for fourth-quarter 1987, reducing the quarter-to-quarter gain. When only continuing operations are compared, profits were 23 percent higher in the fourth quarter of 1988 than they were a year ago. For its entire fiscal year, <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> reported a profit of $ 522 million, or $ 3.80 a share, up 17 percent from $ 444.7 million, or $ 3.23 a share, in 1987. Sales in fiscal 1988 were $ 3.44 billion, up 20 percent from $ 2.88 billion the previous year. In Disney's biggest division, theme parks and resorts, year-end sales were up 11 percent, to $ 2.04 billion. The company, which does n't release attendance figures, said attendance was down from last year, but that customers spent more. The movie and television division, riding high on the popularity of `` Three Men and a Baby,'' `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>'' and `` Who Framed <PERSON> Roger </PERSON> <PERSON> Rabbit </PERSON>,'' recorded a 31 percent gain in sales, to $ 1.15 billion for the year. An expanding string of stores selling Disney-themed toys and clothes had sales of $ 84.6 million, up 78 percent from last year, when far fewer stores were in operation. Results from <ORGANIZATION> Arvida </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp </ORGANIZATION>, a housing developer in <LOCATION> Boca </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rat